I like that phrasing.

“Talking through myself” conveys something different from “talking to myself.”

To me, it suggests that writing isn’t primarily an internal monologue. It’s a process of letting ideas emerge, testing them externally, refining them, and discovering what you think by expressing them. Many writers, scientists, and designers describe something similar—they don’t feel like they’re merely reporting finished thoughts, but using language as part of the thinking process.

